4. 'authenticated WS connection via sec-websocket-protocol' (~line 422): ws created at ~line 430, closed at ~line 464. Wrap lines 444-462 (pongPromise setup through expect) in try/finally.

Follow the existing pattern from dispatch-resilience.e2e.ts malformed messages test (~line 778):
```
const rawWs = new WebSocket(...);
await connectPromise;
try {
  // assertions and operations
} finally {
  rawWs.close();
}
```

Keep the WebSocket creation and connect await OUTSIDE the try — only the post-connect logic goes inside try. The finally block just calls ws.close().

For test 3 ('extension detects replaced connection'), the waitForExtensionDisconnected and waitForExtensionConnected calls after ws.close() should remain OUTSIDE the finally block since they need to run after the WS is closed.

